, and we try to find 
\begin_inset Formula $V(x)$
\end_inset

 at thermal equilibrium, requiring local charge neutrality everywhere, and
 assuming zero mobility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So we write
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\rho & =0\\
\int v\,\rho & =0
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of course, we need boundary conditions, either on 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{E}$
\end_inset

.
 We enforce 
